---
import FaqAccordion from '@/components/FaqAccordion.astro';
---

<section class="section section--tint hair-faq">
  <div class="container--narrow">

    <h2 class="hair-faq__heading">Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <FaqAccordion
      items={[
        {
          question: "Which hair treatment is right for me?",
          answer_html: "<p>The best treatment depends on your specific concerns. HydraFacial Keravive is ideal for scalp health and diffuse thinning, while PRP Hair Restoration is best for stimulating new follicle growth. Your consultation with our medical team will help determine the right path for your unique hair profile.</p>"
        },
        {
          question: "How do these treatments work together?",
          answer_html: "<p>HydraFacial Keravive and PRP can be used as a complementary protocol. Keravive optimizes scalp health and creates an ideal environment for growth, while PRP delivers growth factors directly to the follicles. Our medical team can design a phased plan that combines both for maximum results.</p>"
        },
        {
          question: "How many sessions will I need?",
          answer_html: "<p>Most clients see optimal results after a series of 3&ndash;6 sessions, spaced 4 weeks apart. Your provider will create a personalized treatment plan based on your response and hair restoration goals.</p>"
        },
        {
          question: "How much do PRP and HydraFacial Keravive hair treatments cost?",
          answer_html: "<p>PRP hair restoration is $800 per session, with a recommended series of 3 sessions. HydraFacial Keravive is $500 per session, or $1,295 for a series of 3 treatments. Your exact plan and total are confirmed at your consultation, based on the sessions recommended for your goals. See full details on our <a href=\"/platelet-rich-plasma-hair-millburn/\">PRP hair restoration</a> and <a href=\"/hydrafacial-keravive/\">HydraFacial Keravive</a> pages.</p>"
        },
        {
          question: "How soon will I see results?",
          answer_html: "<p>Initial improvements in scalp health and hair texture are typically noticeable within 4&ndash;6 weeks. More significant improvements in hair density are usually visible at 3&ndash;6 months, as the follicle growth cycle progresses.</p>"
        },
        {
          question: "Who performs my hair treatments?",
          answer_html: "<p>All hair restoration treatments at Menon Medispa are performed by our licensed medical professionals under the supervision of Dr. Aditi Menon, MD, ensuring clinical precision and safety throughout your care.</p>"
        }
      ]}
    />

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hair-faq__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    font-weight: var(--weight-regular);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .hair-faq :global(.faq-accordion__heading) {
    display: none;
  }
</style>
